[96m/*****************************************************************

llist& [93moperator[m=([38;5;121mconst[m llist & origlist)
{

    newlist -> start = origlist;
    [93mreturn[m *newlist;
}

    {[14;9Hstream << [95m"Account Number: "[m << current -> accountno << [95m"[m[38;5;224m\n[m[95m"[m << [95m"Name: "[m << current -> name << [95m"[m[38;5;224m\n[m[95m"[m << [95m"Address::[15;1H "[m << endl << current -> address << [95m"[m[38;5;224m\n[m[95m"[m;[16;9Hcurrent = current -> next;
    }
    [93mreturn[m stream
}

/*****************************************************************
//
//  Function name: friend ostream& operator<<
//
//  DESCRIPTION:   Overload of the << operator in the ostream class
//                 to print all data from the llist. 
//

//                 list (const llist&): The list being printed from.
/y
//  Return Values: ostream&: the stream being written to.
//
****************************************************************/

friend ostream& llist::operator<<(ostream& stream, const llist& list)
{  
    record *current = list.start;
    
    if (list.start == NULL)
    {
        stream << [m[1CThere is currently no accounts in the database.\n\n[1C[95m;
    }
    while (current != NULL)
    {  
        stream << [m[1CAccount Number: [1C[95m << current -> accountno << [m[1C\n[1C[95m << [m[1CNamm[34;1He: [1C[95m << current -> name << [m[1C\n[1C[95m << [m[1CAddress: [1C[95m << endl << current -> addresss[35;1H << [m[1C\n[1C[95m;
        current = current -> next;
    }
    return stream;
}[m[41;64H9[6;39H[?12l[?25h[?25l[38;5;224m\ [m[2C[95m [m[41;63H40[6;40H[?12l[?25h[?25l[38;5;224m0[m[3C[95m [m[41;64H1[6;41H[?12l[?25h[?25l[38;5;224m\ [m[2C[95m [m[41;64H2[6;42H[?12l[?25h[?25l[95m  [m[6;45H[K[41;64H1[6;41H[?12l[?25h[?25l[95m"[m   
[97m[101m}[m
